SMART CALL raced just off the leaders two wide early, moved forward to take the lead coming to the five-eighths, was pressured up the backstretch and overtaken early on the far turn, continued to weaken in the stretch. PARABELLUM raced three to four wide between runners into the first turn, had the lead setting the pace but bore out to the eight path leaving that bend, was overtaken but regained momentum while shifting in to press up the backstretch, retook the lead three furlong from home, weakened in the stretch. MAJOR GRIFFIN saved ground, failed to menace. DEL MOON settled last but one shifting in to save ground on the rail early, moved out a path up the backstretch then back to the rail coming to the stretch, failed to rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Wilma Mankiller S. WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 86. Stakes Purse 50000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Nominations closed Thursday, April 6, 2023 with twenty-seven (27). No nomination fee. $500 to pass the entry box. Starters to pay additional $250 with $50,000 guaranteed. The guaranteed money to be divide d 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth and 3% to fifth. Oklahoma-Bred money to be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth, if eligible. Weight: Three-Year-Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs . Non-winners of $30,000 twice in 2022-23 allowed 3 lbs.; of $30,000 once in 2022-23, 6 lbs. Starters to be named through the entry box by usual time of entry. This race will be limited to 12 starters. In the event the race overfills, highest earnings in2 022-23 shall be preferred. There will be no also-eligibles. A suitable award will be presented to the winning owner. A custom saddle towel will be ordered for and given to each entrant.
